# Expo Router — File-Based Routing Rule

You are an expert in expo-router v6 (SDK 54+) file-based routing for React Native apps.

## Route Directory

- All route files live under `src/app/` (configured via `expo-router` plugin in `app.json`, root not overridden).
- Entry point: `index.js` at project root uses `<ExpoRoot>` from `expo-router`.
- The root layout is `src/app/_layout.tsx`.
- **Never** place route files outside `src/app/`.

## File-Based Route Conventions

| File | Generated Route |
|---|---|
| `src/app/_layout.tsx` | Root layout (wraps all routes) |
| `src/app/index.tsx` | `/` (entry route) |
| `src/app/settings.tsx` | `/settings` |
| `src/app/entry/[id].tsx` | `/entry/:id` (dynamic segment) |
| `src/app/(auth)/_layout.tsx` | Route group layout (no path segment) |
| `src/app/(auth)/unlock.tsx` | `/unlock` (inside group) |
| `src/app/(tabs)/dashboard.tsx` | `/dashboard` (inside group) |

**Route Groups** (`(name)`) — parentheses mean the directory name is **not** part of the URL path. Use for:
- `(auth)` — onboarding, setup, unlock screens (no tab bar)
- `(tabs)` — main app screens with tab navigation

## Layout Files (`_layout.tsx`)

Layouts are **nested** — every directory can have a `_layout.tsx`.

### Root Layout (`src/app/_layout.tsx`)

The root layout must export a **default component** that wraps children. Use `<Stack>` for top-level navigation between route groups:

```typescript
import { Stack } from "expo-router";

export default function RootLayout() {
  return (
    <Stack screenOptions={{ headerShown: false }}>
      <Stack.Screen name="(auth)" options={{ animation: "none" }} />
      <Stack.Screen name="(tabs)" options={{ animation: "none" }} />
    </Stack>
  );
}
```

### Group Layout (`src/app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx`)

Use `<Tabs>` from `expo-router` for tab navigation. When using a **custom bottom nav**, hide the built-in tab bar:

```typescript
import { Tabs } from "expo-router";

export default function TabsLayout() {
  return (
    <Tabs
      backBehavior="history"
      screenOptions={{
        headerShown: false,
        tabBarStyle: { display: 'none' },
      }}
    >
      <Tabs.Screen name="dashboard" />
      <Tabs.Screen name="vault" />
      <Tabs.Screen name="generator" />
      <Tabs.Screen name="health" />
      <Tabs.Screen name="settings" />
    </Tabs>
  );
}
```

### Auth Stack Layout (`src/app/(auth)/_layout.tsx`)

Use `<Stack>` for auth flow screens with header hidden:

```typescript
import { Stack } from "expo-router";

export default function AuthLayout() {
  return (
    <Stack
      screenOptions={{
        headerShown: false,
        contentStyle: { backgroundColor: theme.colors.background },
      }}
    />
  );
}
```

## Navigator Components

Always import navigator components from `expo-router` only — never from `@react-navigation/*`:

| Component | Usage |
|---|---|
| `Stack` | Push/pop navigation (root, auth flows, modal stacks) |
| `Tabs` | Bottom tab navigation |
| `Redirect` | Declarative redirect (render to navigate) |

```typescript
import { Stack, Tabs, Redirect } from "expo-router";
```

## Navigation Hooks

Import all navigation hooks from `expo-router`:

| Hook | Purpose | Example |
|---|---|---|
| `useRouter()` | Programmatic navigation | `router.push(path)`, `router.replace(path)`, `router.back()` |
| `useLocalSearchParams()` | Read URL params from the current route | `const { id } = useLocalSearchParams<{ id?: string }>()` |
| `useGlobalSearchParams()` | Read params from the full URL | `const { tab } = useGlobalSearchParams()` |
| `usePathname()` | Get current path string | `const path = usePathname()` |
| `useSegments()` | Get current path segments array | `const segments = useSegments()` |
| `useFocusEffect()` | Run effect on screen focus | `useFocusEffect(useCallback(() => { ... }, []))` |
| `useNavigation()` | Access native navigation object | For advanced use cases |

## Navigation Methods (`useRouter()`)

```typescript
const router = useRouter();

router.push("/dashboard");         // Navigate forward
router.replace("/unlock");         // Replace current route (no back)
router.back();                     // Go back
router.navigate("/entry/abc123");  // Navigate to dynamic route
router.setParams({ id: "newId" }); // Update current route params
router.reload();                   // Reload current route
router.canGoBack();                // Check if back is available
router.dismiss(2);                 // Dismiss screens (modal stack)
```

## Redirect Pattern

Use `<Redirect>` for **declarative** redirects (render-based):

```typescript
import { Redirect } from "expo-router";

export default function Dashboard() {
  if (!isUnlocked) return <Redirect href="/unlock" />;
  return <DashboardScreen />;
}
```

Use `router.replace()` for **imperative** redirects (after async operations):

```typescript
async function handleUnlock(password: string) {
  await unlockVault(password);
  router.replace("/dashboard");
}
```

## Dynamic Routes

- `src/app/entry/[id].tsx` → matches `/entry/:id`
- Read params with `useLocalSearchParams()`:

```typescript
import { useLocalSearchParams } from "expo-router";

export default function EntryDetail() {
  const { id } = useLocalSearchParams<{ id?: string }>();
}
```

## Typed Routes

This project has `"typedRoutes": true` in `app.json` experiments, enabling TypeScript autocomplete for route paths.

- Use string literals: `"/dashboard"`, `"/unlock"`, `"/entry/abc"`
- For dynamic routes, pass params via object:

```typescript
router.push({ pathname: "/entry/[id]", params: { id: credential.id } });
```

## Path Aliases

This project uses `@/` to map to `src/` in `tsconfig.json`:

```typescript
import { DashboardScreen } from "@/components/screens/dashboard";
import { useVault } from "@/contexts/vault-context";
```

Use `@/` for all imports from `src/`. Use `@/assets/` for asset imports.

## Screen Export Convention

Every route file **must** have a **default export** of a React component:

```typescript
export default function Dashboard() { ... }
```

Named exports are not recognized as routes.

## Key Rules

1. **Always import from `expo-router`**, never from `@react-navigation/*` directly (SDK 54+).
2. Route files must be in `src/app/` directory.
3. Every route directory can have a `_layout.tsx` to wrap child routes.
4. Use route groups `(name)` for organization without affecting URL paths.
5. Dynamic segments use `[param]` syntax in filenames.
6. Prefer `<Redirect>` for declarative guards, `router.replace()` for imperative navigation after async work.
7. Use `useLocalSearchParams<T>()` with a generic type for typed URL params.
8. Always provide `screenOptions` on navigators for consistent animation and appearance.
9. When using a custom tab bar, set `tabBarStyle: { display: 'none' }` on `<Tabs>`.
10. Avoid hardcoding navigation logic inside components — use context-based route guards.

## Layout Nesting Example

```
src/app/
├── _layout.tsx                    # Root Stack
├── index.tsx                      # / (onboarding)
├── (auth)/
│   ├── _layout.tsx                # Auth Stack
│   ├── setup.tsx                  # /setup
│   └── unlock.tsx                 # /unlock
├── (tabs)/
│   ├── _layout.tsx                # Tabs layout (hidden tab bar)
│   ├── dashboard.tsx              # /dashboard
│   ├── vault.tsx                  # /vault
│   ├── generator.tsx              # /generator
│   ├── health.tsx                 # /health
│   └── settings.tsx               # /settings
├── add-credential.tsx             # /add-credential
├── change-password.tsx            # /change-password
└── entry/
    └── [id].tsx                   # /entry/:id
```

